cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.SE

This paper deals with the problem of selecting an appropriate algorithm and its hyperparameters for data analysis, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of a reward function and the reduction of the problem to the multi-armed bandit problem, which are concepts related to reinforcement learning, making cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper involves experiments on real datasets, which could also make cs.SE (Software Engineering) a relevant sub-category.
